<head>WILL</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">意志</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>ORGAN of INTENTION.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>志願</p>
<p>心願</p>
<p>志</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
<div type="old-chinese-contrasts">
<p>Note that neither pre-Christian Greek nor pre-Buddhist Chinese had a notion of an AUTONOMOUS organ of the will. 志 is "main content of one's intentions&gt; aspiration" and very rarely the agency of the will.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
